<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Sphaeralcea</i> <i>ambigua</i> is dominant or characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Bromus</i> <i>rubens</i>, <i>Cryptantha</i> spp., <i>Descurainia</i> <i>pinnata</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>inflatum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>nidularium</i>, <i>Erodium</i> <i>cicutarium</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> spp. and/or <i>Salvia</i> <i>columbariae</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is sparse to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Sphaeralcea ambigua</i> or <i>Descurainia pinnata </i>characteristically present and variable in cover (Evens et al. 2014).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Valley bottoms, channel beds to summits, especially in post-burn areas and along rocky lava flows.  </div>
</div>

        
